			<ns0:name>erik...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/104389777848534510881/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">From a customer report: (I haven't verified)

It seems that NACL does not provide an easy mechanism for accessing the offset of the user's location (in hours) from GMT. There is an implementation of c-library 'localtime' function, but it seems to return values hardwired to GMTOFFSET= 0, meaning it behaves the same as c-library function 'gmtime' on the NACL platform. 
